Police in the Eastern Cape say they're shocked after the killing of six people, including children, on Tuesday night. Police Spokesperson Brigadier Tembinkosi Kinana has the details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police in the Eastern Cape say they are shocked after the killing of six people, including children, on Tuesday night. "The deceased persons include a 42-year-old mother and her children aged between six months and ten-years-old," read a statement from the police. READ: Four family members killed in farm attack It is alleged that an axe was found on the scene of the crime. Police say the circumstances surrounding the incident are currently under investigation.